<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=100154088347036></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100154088347036><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=item.html?item=3927&mid=100154088347036>quick swiching</a> <a id=fs8 href=item.html?item=3927&mid=100154088347036#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=104222><span id= >qweller</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>1 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Sep 26th 5:48 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[3.50]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I think I have an easy way to switch, I use it all the time.&nbsp;&nbsp;I just made "hot buttons" out of my range slot and my first general slots.  I put them at the bottom of my hot button list.  <br><br>Normally, I leave the book in the range slot at all times.  When I want to shoot my bow, I just pick it up from the hot button, click once on the range slot hot button, fire the bow (another hot button, of course), click again to swap back and then return the bow to the gerneral slot.<br><br>This may sound a bit complex, but it couldn't be easier.  Note that you never actually have to put the book into the general slot, just hold it with cursor as you hit the "range attack" key.  Just click-click, fire, click-click.<br><br>Hope this is useful,<br><br>  - Qweller<br><br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
