<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=101614380533925></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f101614380533925><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=item.html?item=3927&mid=101614380533925>RE: quick swiching</a> <a id=fs8 href=item.html?item=3927&mid=101614380533925#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=18005><span id= >Balker</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>50 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Mar 14th 5:12 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[2.85]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Aye, this is a good strategy for medium and small races that can't slam.&nbsp;&nbsp;As a warrior I us dual weild, prior to level 55 I had no way to interupt mob's casting so I kept a sheil in an open inv slot.  When I say &quot;MobX begins casting..&quot; I swapped the sheid into 2nd melee, hit bash, and swap the 1h weapon back in.  Worked great.  At first it's awkward but you get the hang of it.  At level 55, warrior's kick will stun, no need for sheild anymore.<br><br>Balker Neehigh<br>Warlord<br>The Commune<br>Xegony<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
